
Problem Statement  : Student–Course System
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
A college wants to develop a backend system to manage students and the courses they are enrolled in. Each student is enrolled in one course, while a course can have multiple students.

The application should be built using ASP.NET Core Web API with Entity Framework Core to handle database operations.

The system should:

Store Course details (CourseId, CourseName)
Store Student details (StudentId, StudentName, CourseId)
Implement a one-to-many relationship between Course and Student using a foreign key
Provide APIs to:
Add courses
Add students linked to a course
Fetch student data along with course details

The goal is to demonstrate how foreign key relationships, navigation properties, and data retrieval using Include() work in Entity Framework Core.
